The paper deals with the problem of recovering sparse vectors from underdetermined measurements, which is a common topic in the fields of information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and statistics (cs.SI). The paper proposes a new algorithm that approximates the $\ell_0$ norm with a series of concave functions, and provides theoretical analyses and numerical simulations to support its performance. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT, cs.LG, and cs.SP, followed by cs.NA and cs.SI.
